-[ ] Fix escaping order + identifier sanitising; wire build-time regen.

### Blockers
 -  None.

##  Outcome
 -  *LANDED `23d71efc`* (2026-06-16): js2c.js now escapes `\` FIRST, then `"`,
    then `\t`/`\r`/other C0 controls (`\xNN`), preserving the `\n"\n"` line-split;
    the C identifier is sanitised (`[^A-Za-z0-9_]`→`_`, digit-leading gets a `_`
    prefix). Verified by jabc-eval round-trip (backslash/regex/tab/CR/control/
    digit-name cases all reconstruct the original bytes; buggy vs fixed shown for a
    `\d`-input). Blobs (`io.js.c`/`test.js.c`) are NOT regenerated (node absent) and
    stay byte-identical — they benefit only on the next node-driven regen; currently
    correct only because the existing `.js` sources contain no bare backslashes.
    Build-time regen step deferred (still needs node in the toolchain).
 -  (filed 2026-06-16 from the js/ 7-lens review)

